{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S3gGyj1p3UynHjLTMSgK7B","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Project Overview:\nThis is a Quarkus-based Real World API service (a typical backend for a blog/social platform) with the following key characteristics:\n\n1. Architecture:\n   - Clean Architecture with layers:\n     - Domain Layer: Models, Features, Repositories\n     - Application Layer: Web resources, DTOs\n     - Infrastructure Layer: Hibernate repositories, JPA entities, configuration\n\n2. Technologies:\n   - Framework: Quarkus (with Jakarta EE)\n   - ORM: Hibernate with Panache\n   - Database: PostgreSQL\n   - Security: JWT-based authentication\n   - Validation: Hibernate Validator\n   - Dependency Injection: CDI\n   - Build: Maven\n\n3. Key Domains:\n   - Users\n   - Articles\n   - Comments\n   - Profiles\n   - Tags\n\n4. Features:\n   - User registration/authentication\n   - Article CRUD operations\n   - Commenting on articles\n   - Favoriting articles\n   - Following users\n   - Tagging articles\n\n5. Configuration:\n   - Uses PostgreSQL\n   - JWT authentication with public/private key pair\n   - Quarkus-specific configuration\n\n6. Deployment Options:\n   - JVM mode Dockerfile\n   - Native image Dockerfile\n\n7. Testing:\n   - Integration tests for all major resources\n   - Uses RestAssured for HTTP testing\n\nThe project follows a clean, modular design with clear separation of concerns, making it a good example of a real-world Quarkus application implementing a blog/social platform backend.\n\nShall I elaborate on any specific aspect of the project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"c1c46d99-53d4-4b4a-ac5a-6f48334f0b3a"}
