{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012cNwimaKswks2BrXCPn7Hk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import io.smallrye.jwt.build.Jwt;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import java.util.*;\n     6→\n     7→@ApplicationScoped\n     8→public class JwtTokenProvider {\n     9→\n    10→  public String createUserToken(String subject) {\n    11→    return Jwt.issuer(\"users-service\")\n    12→        .subject(subject)\n    13→        .groups(new HashSet<>(List.of(\"USER\")))\n    14→        .sign();\n    15→  }\n    16→}\n    17→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"2fbe012a-5a2b-445b-971f-a76217cf0995"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D5JWjM6dgiQ1PoTVJbQzPW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.elytron.security.common.BcryptUtil;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     6→\n     7→@ApplicationScoped\n     8→public class BCryptHashProvider implements HashProvider {\n     9→\n    10→  @Override\n    11→  public String hashPassword(String password) {\n    12→    return BcryptUtil.bcryptHash(password);\n    13→  }\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public boolean checkPassword(String plaintext, String hashed) {\n    17→    return BcryptUtil.matches(plaintext, hashed);\n    18→  }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"3928468c-d20f-4335-952a-4ab5c5a11db6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FP8398w28a4E75mPxaruao","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     7→\n     8→@ApplicationScoped\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class SlugifySlugProvider implements SlugProvider {\n    11→\n    12→  private final Slugify slugify;\n    13→\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public String slugify(String text) {\n    16→    return slugify.slugify(text);\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"6043d190-1019-4901-b64a-ef605f488fc3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ATkmAsamtVuDfoJRAQzes4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.configuration;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.SerializationFeature;\n     6→import com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype.jsr310.JavaTimeModule;\n     7→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     9→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n    10→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    12→\n    13→@Dependent\n    14→public class ApplicationConfiguration {\n    15→\n    16→  @Produces\n    17→  @Singleton\n    18→  public Slugify slugify() {\n    19→    return Slugify.builder().build();\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  @Singleton\n    23→  @Produces\n    24→  public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n    25→    ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    26→    objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    27→    objectMapper.enable(DeserializationFeature.UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE);\n    28→    objectMapper.registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    29→    return objectMapper;\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @Singleton\n    33→  @Produces\n    34→  @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper\n    35→  public ObjectMapper noWrapRootValueObjectMapper() {\n    36→    return new ObjectMapper().registerModule(new JavaTimeModule());\n    37→  }\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"e081f679-b892-4fca-90e8-9837b3d1d8e8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QVZtziTUWwYSCk4trGzaEu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.configuration;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl.*;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n    14→\n    15→@Dependent\n    16→public class UsersConfiguration {\n    17→\n    18→  @Produces\n    19→  @Singleton\n    20→  public CreateUser createUser(\n    21→      UserRepository userRepository, HashProvider hashProvider, UserModelBuilder userBuilder) {\n    22→    return new CreateUserImpl(userRepository, hashProvider, userBuilder);\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  @Produces\n    26→  @Singleton\n    27→  public UpdateUser updateUser(\n    28→      FindUserById findUserById, UserRepository userRepository, ModelValidator modelValidator) {\n    29→    return new UpdateUserImpl(findUserById, userRepository, modelValidator);\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @Produces\n    33→  @Singleton\n    34→  public FindUserById findUserById(UserRepository userRepository) {\n    35→    return new FindUserByIdImpl(userRepository);\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  @Produces\n    39→  @Singleton\n    40→  public LoginUser loginUser(UserRepository userRepository, HashProvider hashProvider) {\n    41→    return new LoginUserImpl(userRepository, hashProvider);\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  @Produces\n    45→  @Singleton\n    46→  public FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername(UserRepository userRepository) {\n    47→    return new FindUserByUsernameImpl(userRepository);\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  @Produces\n    51→  @Singleton\n    52→  public IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser(FollowRelationshipRepository usersFollowedRepository) {\n    53→    return new IsFollowingUserImpl(usersFollowedRepository);\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  @Produces\n    57→  @Singleton\n    58→  public FollowUserByUsername followUserByUsername(\n    59→      FindUserById findUserById,\n    60→      FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername,\n    61→      FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository) {\n    62→    return new FollowUserByUsernameImpl(\n    63→        findUserById, findUserByUsername, followRelationshipRepository);\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  @Produces\n    67→  @Singleton\n    68→  public UnfollowUserByUsername unfollowUserByUsername(\n    69→      FindUserById findUserById,\n    70→      FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername,\n    71→      FollowRelationshipRepository followRelationshipRepository) {\n    72→    return new UnfollowUserByUsernameImpl(\n    73→        findUserById, findUserByUsername, followRelationshipRepository);\n    74→  }\n    75→\n    76→  @Produces\n    77→  @Singleton\n    78→  public UserModelBuilder userModelBuilder(ModelValidator modelValidator) {\n    79→    return new UserModelBuilder(modelValidator);\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  @Produces\n    83→  @Singleton\n    84→  public ModelValidator modelValidator(Validator validator) {\n    85→    return new ModelValidator(validator);\n    86→  }\n    87→}\n    88→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"5fa2f550-7203-4d99-ac0d-8693bcbb5c3a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014kkg7cTgc6Ei1X1wbW9P9z","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→quarkus.rest.path=/api\n     2→\n     3→# Database configuration — PostgreSQL for all profiles.\n     4→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n     5→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/realworld\n     6→quarkus.datasource.username=realworld\n     7→quarkus.datasource.password=realworld\n     8→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n     9→\n    10→# JWT settings\n    11→smallrye.jwt.sign.key.location=classpath:privateKey.pem\n    12→mp.jwt.verify.publickey.location=classpath:publicKey.pem\n    13→mp.jwt.verify.issuer=users-service\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"e817e96a-2281-498c-980e-d40274cdf9f5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G26AD5uVbUBs9b2kfHvHTy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/bin/bash\n     2→set -e\n     3→\n     4→# Start PostgreSQL\n     5→pg_ctlcluster $(pg_lsclusters -h | head -1 | awk '{print $1, $2}') start\n     6→\n     7→# Create database and user\n     8→su - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"CREATE USER realworld WITH PASSWORD 'realworld';\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\n     9→su - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"CREATE DATABASE realworld OWNER realworld;\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    10→su - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE realworld TO realworld;\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    11→\n    12→exec java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"2be9f5f0-dc9a-4f51-80ff-1fbfd7aa179c"}
