{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013eZvhW258EDS9oxDRdv9pw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     4→import java.util.UUID;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     7→\n     8→@Named\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class UserModelBuilder {\n    11→  private final ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    12→\n    13→  public User build(String username, String email, String password) {\n    14→    return modelValidator.validate(\n    15→        new User(UUID.randomUUID(), username, email, password, null, null));\n    16→  }\n    17→\n    18→  public User build(\n    19→      UUID id, String username, String bio, String image, String password, String email) {\n    20→    return modelValidator.validate(new User(id, username, email, password, bio, image));\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"0ae35cdf-d0ac-43fe-bce6-c8fcf5fa5a2a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LS3sTSKAu2h4c9WEopGZza","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.util.UUID;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     8→\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class ArticleModelBuilder {\n    11→\n    12→  private final ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    13→\n    14→  public Article build(String slug, String title, String description, String body, User author) {\n    15→    final var createdAt = LocalDateTime.now();\n    16→    return modelValidator.validate(\n    17→        new Article(\n    18→            UUID.randomUUID(), slug, title, description, body, createdAt, createdAt, author));\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public Article build(\n    22→      UUID id,\n    23→      String slug,\n    24→      String title,\n    25→      String description,\n    26→      String body,\n    27→      LocalDateTime createdAt,\n    28→      LocalDateTime updatedAt,\n    29→      User author) {\n    30→    return modelValidator.validate(\n    31→        new Article(id, slug, title, description, body, createdAt, updatedAt, author));\n    32→  }\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"0f379d60-8f28-4f3b-b7f4-968f52886e1d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019R7midpRgS5WNfkkZSHekX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     5→import java.util.Set;\n     6→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     7→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ModelValidationException;\n     9→\n    10→@AllArgsConstructor\n    11→public class ModelValidator {\n    12→\n    13→  private final Validator validator;\n    14→\n    15→  public <T> T validate(T model) {\n    16→    Set<ConstraintViolation<T>> constraintViolations = validator.validate(model);\n    17→\n    18→    if (!constraintViolations.isEmpty()) {\n    19→      final var messages =\n    20→          constraintViolations.stream()\n    21→              .map(ConstraintViolation::getMessage)\n    22→              .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    23→      throw new ModelValidationException(messages);\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    return model;\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"2a4d5cef-32df-4287-9211-28586daea026"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ESehJck7u5ZQ8wZPU9JTQY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.EmailAlreadyExistsException;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UsernameAlreadyExistsException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateUser;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.CreateUserInput;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    12→\n    13→@AllArgsConstructor\n    14→public class CreateUserImpl implements CreateUser {\n    15→\n    16→  private final UserRepository userRepository;\n    17→  private final HashProvider hashProvider;\n    18→  private final UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    19→\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public User handle(CreateUserInput createUserInput) {\n    22→    final var user =\n    23→        userBuilder.build(\n    24→            createUserInput.getUsername(),\n    25→            createUserInput.getEmail(),\n    26→            createUserInput.getPassword());\n    27→    checkExistingUsername(user.getUsername());\n    28→    checkExistingEmail(user.getEmail());\n    29→    user.setPassword(hashProvider.hashPassword(user.getPassword()));\n    30→    userRepository.save(user);\n    31→    return user;\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  private void checkExistingUsername(String username) {\n    35→    if (userRepository.existsBy(\"username\", username)) {\n    36→      throw new UsernameAlreadyExistsException();\n    37→    }\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  private void checkExistingEmail(String email) {\n    41→    if (userRepository.existsBy(\"email\", email)) {\n    42→      throw new EmailAlreadyExistsException();\n    43→    }\n    44→  }\n    45→}\n    46→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"0de3499b-0d47-4d2b-9b16-dc399be4e68f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012xATZ5fqryQ7dC8XCAED15","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     4→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.InvalidPasswordException;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.UserNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.LoginUser;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.HashProvider;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.LoginUserInput;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    11→\n    12→@AllArgsConstructor\n    13→public class LoginUserImpl implements LoginUser {\n    14→\n    15→  private final UserRepository userRepository;\n    16→  private final HashProvider hashProvider;\n    17→\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public User handle(LoginUserInput loginUserInput) {\n    20→    final var user =\n    21→        userRepository\n    22→            .findByEmail(loginUserInput.getEmail())\n    23→            .orElseThrow(UserNotFoundException::new);\n    24→    if (!isPasswordValid(loginUserInput.getPassword(), user.getPassword())) {\n    25→      throw new InvalidPasswordException();\n    26→    }\n    27→    return user;\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  private boolean isPasswordValid(String password, String hashedPassword) {\n    31→    return hashProvider.checkPassword(password, hashedPassword);\n    32→  }\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"4546c524-6570-45c3-bbf5-dd2903256b26"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014NumieWJWNjjAxcaXfvgqg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateArticle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.*;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    11→\n    12→@AllArgsConstructor\n    13→public class CreateArticleImpl implements CreateArticle {\n    14→\n    15→  private final FindUserById findUserById;\n    16→  private final ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    17→  private final ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    18→  private final CreateSlugByTitle createSlugByTitle;\n    19→  private final FindTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists findTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists;\n    20→  private final TagRelationshipRepository tagRelationshipRepository;\n    21→\n    22→  @Override\n    23→  public Article handle(NewArticleInput newArticleInput) {\n    24→    final var author = findUserById.handle(newArticleInput.authorId());\n    25→    final var slug = createSlugByTitle.handle(newArticleInput.title());\n    26→    final var article =\n    27→        articleBuilder.build(\n    28→            slug,\n    29→            newArticleInput.title(),\n    30→            newArticleInput.description(),\n    31→            newArticleInput.body(),\n    32→            author);\n    33→    articleRepository.save(article);\n    34→    final var tags = findTagsByNameCreateIfNotExists.handle(newArticleInput.tagList());\n    35→    createTagRelationship(article, tags);\n    36→    return article;\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  private void createTagRelationship(Article article, List<Tag> tags) {\n    40→    tags.forEach(tag -> tagRelationshipRepository.save(new TagRelationship(article, tag)));\n    41→  }\n    42→}\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lax6KudpuM6K69kRMBQEAG","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"1a202bdc-48af-4789-b16c-7806bf2a1909"}
