{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XTefZgGW8eeDpDq5wKgsZH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→import java.util.HashSet;\n     6→import java.util.Set;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.JwtAuthFilter;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.BusinessExceptionMapper;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.ValidationExceptionMapper;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.CorsFilter;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.JacksonConfig;\n    13→\n    14→@ApplicationPath(\"/\")\n    15→public class RealWorldApplication extends Application {\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public Set<Class<?>> getClasses() {\n    19→        Set<Class<?>> classes = new HashSet<>();\n    20→        // Resources\n    21→        classes.add(ArticlesResource.class);\n    22→        classes.add(UsersResource.class);\n    23→        classes.add(UserResource.class);\n    24→        classes.add(ProfilesResource.class);\n    25→        classes.add(TagsResource.class);\n    26→        classes.add(HealthResource.class);\n    27→\n    28→        // Providers\n    29→        classes.add(JwtAuthFilter.class);\n    30→        classes.add(BusinessExceptionMapper.class);\n    31→        classes.add(ValidationExceptionMapper.class);\n    32→        classes.add(CorsFilter.class);\n    33→        classes.add(JacksonConfig.class);\n    34→\n    35→        return classes;\n    36→    }\n    37→}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to im