{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ANSXsgYiswphrgFTEEpNwW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me rewrite all the Panache repositories to use standard JPA. I'll use a Task agent since there are many files:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1609,"cache_read_input_tokens":107267,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1609,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1662},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"b73aaaf1-8330-4e6c-9b11-830384823c7e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ANSXsgYiswphrgFTEEpNwW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01LCBNthBJ7SZpqr62bdGvHP","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Rewrite all Panache repositories","prompt":"I need you to rewrite all the Panache repository files to use standard JPA EntityManager instead of Quarkus Panache APIs.\n\nThe base directory is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output\n\nThe AbstractPanacheRepository has already been rewritten to:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.*;\n\npublic abstract class AbstractPanacheRepository<ENTITY, ID> {\n\n    @Inject\n    protected EntityManager em;\n\n    protected EntityManager getEntityManager() {\n        return em;\n    }\n\n    protected UserEntity findUserEntityById(UUID id) { return em.find(UserEntity.class, id); }\n    protected TagEntity findTagEntityById(UUID id) { return em.find(TagEntity.class, id); }\n    protected ArticleEntity findArticleEntityById(UUID id) { return em.find(ArticleEntity.class, id); }\n    protected CommentEntity findCommentEntityById(UUID id) { return em.find(CommentEntity.class, id); }\n    protected FavoriteRelationshipEntity findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) { ... }\n    protected boolean isNotEmpty(List<?> list) { ... }\n    protected List<String> toUpperCase(List<String> subjectList) { ... }\n}\n```\n\nNow I need you to REWRITE each of these files, replacing ALL Panache API calls with standard JPA EntityManager queries:\n\n**Panache methods to replace:**\n- `find(\"query\", params)` → `em.createQuery(\"FROM Entity WHERE query\", Entity.class).setParameter(...)`\n- `find(\"field\", value).firstResultOptional()` → JPQL query with `getResultStream().findFirst()`\n- `count(\"query\", params)` → `em.createQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(e) FROM Entity e WHERE ...\", Long.class)`\n- `count(\"field\", value)` → similar count query\n- `persist(entity)` / `persistAndFlush(entity)` → `em.persist(entity)` / `em.persist(entity); em.flush()`\n- `findByIdOptional(id)` → `Optional.ofNullable(em.find(Entity.class, id))`\n- `deleteById(id)` → find then `em.remove(entity)`\n- `delete(entity)` → `em.remove(em.merge(entity))`\n- `listAll()` → `em.createQuery(\"FROM Entity\", Entity.class).getResultList()`\n- `.page(Page.of(offset, limit))` → `.setFirstResult(offset).setMaxResults(limit)`\n- `Parameters.with(\"key\", val)` → `query.setParameter(\"key\", val)`\n- Sort.descending(\"field\") → `ORDER BY field DESC` in JPQL\n- static imports of `io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters.with` → remove\n\nFILES TO REWRITE:\n\n1. **UserRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `count(\"upper(field)\", ...)`, `find(\"upper(email)\", ...)`, `findByIdOptional(id)`, `persist(entity)`, `findById(id)`, `find(\"upper(username)\", ...)`\n\n2. **ArticleRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `count(\"upper(slug)\", ...)`, `persistAndFlush(entity)`, `findByIdOptional(id)`, `find(\"upper(slug)\", ...)`, `find(\"query with params\")`, `deleteById(id)`, `find().page(Page.of(...)).list()`, `Sort.descending()`, `Parameters.with()`\n\n3. **CommentRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `persist(entity)`, `find(\"query\", params)`, `delete(entity)`, `find(\"query\", params).list()`\n\n4. **FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `count(\"query\", params)`, `find(\"query\", params).firstResultOptional()`, `persist(entity)`, `delete(entity)`\n\n5. **FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `count(\"query\", params)`, `persistAndFlush(entity)`, `find(\"primaryKey\", key).firstResultOptional()`, `delete(entity)`\n\n6. **TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `persist(entity)`, `find(\"query\", params).list()`\n\n7. **TagRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `listAll()`, `find(\"upper(name)\", ...).firstResultOptional()`, `persist(entity)`, `find(\"query\", params).list()`\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the current file\n2. Rewrite it completely, replacing all Panache imports and method calls with standard JPA\n3. Write the new file\n\nKeep `@ApplicationScoped` and `@AllArgsConstructor` annotations. Keep the same class hierarchy extending `AbstractPanacheRepository`.\n\nIMPORTANT: When converting Panache shorthand queries like `find(\"upper(slug)\", slug.toUpperCase().trim())`, the Panache convention is that the string is a WHERE clause fragment and the second argument is a positional parameter. So it becomes: `em.createQuery(\"FROM ArticleEntity WHERE upper(slug) = ?1\", ArticleEntity.class).setParameter(1, slug.toUpperCase().trim())`\n\nFor `count(\"upper(slug)\", value)` → `em.createQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(e) FROM ArticleEntity e WHERE upper(e.slug) = ?1\", Long.class).setParameter(1, value).getSingleResult()`\n\nFor named parameters with Parameters.with(): use query.setParameter(\"name\", value) directly.\n\nFor Panache's `find(\"field\", value)` shorthand: this is equivalent to `WHERE field = ?1` with the value as parameter 1.\n\nWRITE ALL 7 FILES.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1609,"cache_read_input_tokens":107267,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1609,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1662},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"5b20f427-8146-4ad9-b0bf-3d3389814187"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need you to rewrite all the Panache repository files to use standard JPA EntityManager instead of Quarkus Panache APIs.\n\nThe base directory is: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output\n\nThe AbstractPanacheRepository has already been rewritten to:\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.*;\n\npublic abstract class AbstractPanacheRepository<ENTITY, ID> {\n\n    @Inject\n    protected EntityManager em;\n\n    protected EntityManager getEntityManager() {\n        return em;\n    }\n\n    protected UserEntity findUserEntityById(UUID id) { return em.find(UserEntity.class, id); }\n    protected TagEntity findTagEntityById(UUID id) { return em.find(TagEntity.class, id); }\n    protected ArticleEntity findArticleEntityById(UUID id) { return em.find(ArticleEntity.class, id); }\n    protected CommentEntity findCommentEntityById(UUID id) { return em.find(CommentEntity.class, id); }\n    protected FavoriteRelationshipEntity findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) { ... }\n    protected boolean isNotEmpty(List<?> list) { ... }\n    protected List<String> toUpperCase(List<String> subjectList) { ... }\n}\n```\n\nNow I need you to REWRITE each of these files, replacing ALL Panache API calls with standard JPA EntityManager queries:\n\n**Panache methods to replace:**\n- `find(\"query\", params)` → `em.createQuery(\"FROM Entity WHERE query\", Entity.class).setParameter(...)`\n- `find(\"field\", value).firstResultOptional()` → JPQL query with `getResultStream().findFirst()`\n- `count(\"query\", params)` → `em.createQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(e) FROM Entity e WHERE ...\", Long.class)`\n- `count(\"field\", value)` → similar count query\n- `persist(entity)` / `persistAndFlush(entity)` → `em.persist(entity)` / `em.persist(entity); em.flush()`\n- `findByIdOptional(id)` → `Optional.ofNullable(em.find(Entity.class, id))`\n- `deleteById(id)` → find then `em.remove(entity)`\n- `delete(entity)` → `em.remove(em.merge(entity))`\n- `listAll()` → `em.createQuery(\"FROM Entity\", Entity.class).getResultList()`\n- `.page(Page.of(offset, limit))` → `.setFirstResult(offset).setMaxResults(limit)`\n- `Parameters.with(\"key\", val)` → `query.setParameter(\"key\", val)`\n- Sort.descending(\"field\") → `ORDER BY field DESC` in JPQL\n- static imports of `io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters.with` → remove\n\nFILES TO REWRITE:\n\n1. **UserRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `count(\"upper(field)\", ...)`, `find(\"upper(email)\", ...)`, `findByIdOptional(id)`, `persist(entity)`, `findById(id)`, `find(\"upper(username)\", ...)`\n\n2. **ArticleRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `count(\"upper(slug)\", ...)`, `persistAndFlush(entity)`, `findByIdOptional(id)`, `find(\"upper(slug)\", ...)`, `find(\"query with params\")`, `deleteById(id)`, `find().page(Page.of(...)).list()`, `Sort.descending()`, `Parameters.with()`\n\n3. **CommentRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `persist(entity)`, `find(\"query\", params)`, `delete(entity)`, `find(\"query\", params).list()`\n\n4. **FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `count(\"query\", params)`, `find(\"query\", params).firstResultOptional()`, `persist(entity)`, `delete(entity)`\n\n5. **FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `count(\"query\", params)`, `persistAndFlush(entity)`, `find(\"primaryKey\", key).firstResultOptional()`, `delete(entity)`\n\n6. **TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `persist(entity)`, `find(\"query\", params).list()`\n\n7. **TagRepositoryPanache.java** - Currently uses: `listAll()`, `find(\"upper(name)\", ...).firstResultOptional()`, `persist(entity)`, `find(\"query\", params).list()`\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the current file\n2. Rewrite it completely, replacing all Panache imports and method calls with standard JPA\n3. Write the new file\n\nKeep `@ApplicationScoped` and `@AllArgsConstructor` annotations. Keep the same class hierarchy extending `AbstractPanacheRepository`.\n\nIMPORTANT: When converting Panache shorthand queries like `find(\"upper(slug)\", slug.toUpperCase().trim())`, the Panache convention is that the string is a WHERE clause fragment and the second argument is a positional parameter. So it becomes: `em.createQuery(\"FROM ArticleEntity WHERE upper(slug) = ?1\", ArticleEntity.class).setParameter(1, slug.toUpperCase().trim())`\n\nFor `count(\"upper(slug)\", value)` → `em.createQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(e) FROM ArticleEntity e WHERE upper(e.slug) = ?1\", Long.class).setParameter(1, value).getSingleResult()`\n\nFor named parameters with Parameters.with(): use query.setParameter(\"name\", value) directly.\n\nFor Panache's `find(\"field\", value)` shorthand: this is equivalent to `WHERE field = ?1` with the value as parameter 1.\n\nWRITE ALL 7 FILES."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LCBNthBJ7SZpqr62bdGvHP","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"c1dbd777-ef2c-463b-b2b2-e5fd7bf72fbd"}
