{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Kj5sCvCzU5yL9MHnFGuEhM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Email;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Pattern;\n     6→import java.util.UUID;\n     7→import lombok.Getter;\n     8→import lombok.Setter;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UpdateUserInput;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.constraint.AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull;\n    12→\n    13→@Getter\n    14→@Setter\n    15→@JsonRootName(\"user\")\n    16→@AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull\n    17→public class UpdateUserRequest {\n    18→\n    19→  @Pattern(regexp = \"\\\\A(?!\\\\s*\\\\Z).+\", message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    20→  private String username;\n    21→\n    22→  private String bio;\n    23→  private String image;\n    24→  @Email private String email;\n    25→\n    26→  public UpdateUserInput toUpdateUserInput(UUID userId) {\n    27→    return new UpdateUserInput(userId, this.username, this.bio, this.image, this.email);\n    28→  }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015XE4YSMXCKgL5Bp2pnLmQb","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"c8ec8c17-789d-429c-ac68-1a51688af4cc"}
