{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WuU3XDaWBsKeSer6S94p5T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me also check if there are any remaining issues. Let me verify the `@AllArgsConstructor` on repositories - with CDI injection, we need to ensure the `@Inject` on the base class `em` field works properly with `@AllArgsConstructor` from Lombok. The issue is that `@AllArgsConstructor` will generate a constructor that takes `EntityUtils` (the declared field) but the `em` field is `@Inject`ed. With Weld CDI, `@AllArgsConstructor` should work if there's also a no-arg constructor. Let me check if the entities have no-arg constructors - actually the CDI spec requires a no-arg constructor or a `@Inject` annotated constructor. Lombok's `@AllArgsConstructor` alone won't suffice for CDI beans.\n\nThis is a critical issue. The CDI container needs a no-arg constructor. Let me fix the repository classes by ensuring they have no-arg constructors. Since `@AllArgsConstructor` is used along with injected fields, the CDI container can't construct these beans. I need to handle this properly.\n\nThe approach: CDI uses field injection (`@Inject`) for `em` (from the base class) and constructor injection for the declared fields. But CDI also needs a no-arg constructor. With `@AllArgsConstructor`, it generates only the all-args constructor. I need to also add `@NoArgsConstructor` or remove `@AllArgsConstructor` and use `@Inject` for all fields.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully: the original code used `@AllArgsConstructor` for Quarkus CDI which supports constructor injection without `@Inject`. In standard CDI (Weld), if a bean has a single constructor with parameters, it might be treated as an `@Inject` constructor (CDI 4.0+). But to be safe, let me add `@Inject` annotation to the generated constructor or just use field injection.\n\nThe simplest approach: Since the `em` field is `@Inject`ed from the base class, and the `EntityUtils` field needs to be injected too, let me convert the repositories to use field injection for `entityUtils` as well. This means removing `@AllArgsConstructor`, making `entityUtils` non-final, and adding `@Inject`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":226,"cache_read_input_tokens":143955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":226,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1847},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"093a82b9-d172-42d7-80a1-9e9a2ed6e858"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WuU3XDaWBsKeSer6S94p5T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_011GSaWpMkzbBq12YDLYD3Fg","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Fix CDI injection for repos","prompt":"I need you to fix CDI injection for all repository classes and the resource/utility classes in the project. The issue is that these classes use Lombok `@AllArgsConstructor` for CDI constructor injection, which worked in Quarkus but won't work reliably in standard Weld CDI.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output\n\nThe fix for REPOSITORY classes (they extend AbstractPanacheRepository which has `@Inject protected EntityManager em`):\n- Remove `@AllArgsConstructor`\n- Change `private final EntityUtils entityUtils;` to `@Inject EntityUtils entityUtils;` (non-final, add @Inject)\n- Import `jakarta.inject.Inject;` if not already imported\n- Remove `lombok.AllArgsConstructor` import if no longer used\n\nFiles to fix (repositories):\n1. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/UserRepositoryPanache.java\n2. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/ArticleRepositoryPanache.java  \n3. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/CommentRepositoryPanache.java\n4. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n5. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n6. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n7. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRepositoryPanache.java\n\nFor the RESOURCE classes (ArticlesResource, UsersResource, UserResource, ProfilesResource, TagsResource), they use `@AllArgsConstructor` for CDI injection. The fix is:\n- Keep `@AllArgsConstructor` BUT also add `@NoArgsConstructor` (CDI needs a no-arg constructor)  \n- Change `private final` fields to just field-level `@Inject` (non-final)\n- OR: simpler approach - remove `@AllArgsConstructor`, add `@Inject` to each field, make them non-final, and add `import jakarta.inject.Inject`\n\nActually, the simplest universal fix is:\n- For ALL classes with `@AllArgsConstructor` that are CDI beans: \n  - Remove `@AllArgsConstructor`\n  - Make all injected fields non-final\n  - Add `@Inject` to each field that needs injection\n  - Ensure `jakarta.inject.Inject` is imported\n\nFiles to fix (resources/utils):\n8. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java\n9. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java\n10. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java\n11. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java\n12. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java\n13. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java\n\nAlso fix providers:\n14. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/SlugifySlugProvider.java\n15. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/entity/EntityUtils.java\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. Remove `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation\n3. Remove `import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;` (if there are no other lombok imports on the same line)\n4. Make all fields non-final \n5. Add `@Inject` annotation to each field that needs CDI injection\n6. Ensure `import jakarta.inject.Inject;` is present\n7. For fields that already have `@Inject`, keep them\n\nIMPORTANT NOTES:\n- In ArticlesResource.java, the field `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper objectMapper` should become `@Inject @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper objectMapper`\n- In TagsResource.java, same for the ObjectMapper field\n- In UsersResource.java, `@Inject private final JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;` should become `@Inject JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;`\n- In UserResource.java, `@Inject JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;` is already correct, just make non-final\n\nWrite ALL modified files.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":226,"cache_read_input_tokens":143955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":226,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1847},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"7cf690e6-bf8d-40fb-a3af-f64bf16cb529"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need you to fix CDI injection for all repository classes and the resource/utility classes in the project. The issue is that these classes use Lombok `@AllArgsConstructor` for CDI constructor injection, which worked in Quarkus but won't work reliably in standard Weld CDI.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output\n\nThe fix for REPOSITORY classes (they extend AbstractPanacheRepository which has `@Inject protected EntityManager em`):\n- Remove `@AllArgsConstructor`\n- Change `private final EntityUtils entityUtils;` to `@Inject EntityUtils entityUtils;` (non-final, add @Inject)\n- Import `jakarta.inject.Inject;` if not already imported\n- Remove `lombok.AllArgsConstructor` import if no longer used\n\nFiles to fix (repositories):\n1. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/UserRepositoryPanache.java\n2. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/ArticleRepositoryPanache.java  \n3. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/CommentRepositoryPanache.java\n4. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n5. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n6. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n7. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRepositoryPanache.java\n\nFor the RESOURCE classes (ArticlesResource, UsersResource, UserResource, ProfilesResource, TagsResource), they use `@AllArgsConstructor` for CDI injection. The fix is:\n- Keep `@AllArgsConstructor` BUT also add `@NoArgsConstructor` (CDI needs a no-arg constructor)  \n- Change `private final` fields to just field-level `@Inject` (non-final)\n- OR: simpler approach - remove `@AllArgsConstructor`, add `@Inject` to each field, make them non-final, and add `import jakarta.inject.Inject`\n\nActually, the simplest universal fix is:\n- For ALL classes with `@AllArgsConstructor` that are CDI beans: \n  - Remove `@AllArgsConstructor`\n  - Make all injected fields non-final\n  - Add `@Inject` to each field that needs injection\n  - Ensure `jakarta.inject.Inject` is imported\n\nFiles to fix (resources/utils):\n8. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ArticlesResource.java\n9. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UsersResource.java\n10. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java\n11. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java\n12. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java\n13. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java\n\nAlso fix providers:\n14. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/SlugifySlugProvider.java\n15. src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/entity/EntityUtils.java\n\nFor each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. Remove `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation\n3. Remove `import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;` (if there are no other lombok imports on the same line)\n4. Make all fields non-final \n5. Add `@Inject` annotation to each field that needs CDI injection\n6. Ensure `import jakarta.inject.Inject;` is present\n7. For fields that already have `@Inject`, keep them\n\nIMPORTANT NOTES:\n- In ArticlesResource.java, the field `@NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper objectMapper` should become `@Inject @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper objectMapper`\n- In TagsResource.java, same for the ObjectMapper field\n- In UsersResource.java, `@Inject private final JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;` should become `@Inject JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;`\n- In UserResource.java, `@Inject JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;` is already correct, just make non-final\n\nWrite ALL modified files."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011GSaWpMkzbBq12YDLYD3Fg","session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"84df0004-c091-43e1-a1b9-a24308c60db8"}
