{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SnteXtaHcBPUSkpBt8WxMW","type":"tool_result","content":"Based on the source code, UndertowJaxrsServer has multiple deploy method signatures that can handle:\n\n1. Deployment with a ResteasyDeployment:\n- `deploy()`: Uses default deployment\n- `deploy(ResteasyDeployment resteasyDeployment)`\n- `deploy(ResteasyDeployment resteasyDeployment, String contextPath, ClassLoader clazzLoader)`\n\n2. Deployment with JAX-RS Application:\n- `deploy(Application application)`\n- `deploy(Application application, String contextPath)`\n- `deploy(Class<? extends Application> application)`\n- `deploy(Class<? extends Application> application, String contextPath)`\n\nThe method expects a ResteasyDeployment, which is typically created using ResteasyDeploymentImpl. The deployment can be configured with an Application instance or Application class, and optionally a context path.\n\nA key quote describes the deployment approach: \"Each ResteasyDeployment or jaxrs Application is deployed under its own web deployment (WAR)\"."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"b5c73514-a601-4f5c-96fa-b2a0940dba79"}
