{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01CgCvFdrW5Xec1swaRRg9dy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK, so the Jandex issue persists AND the code has a class `EntityManagerFactoryProducer` that I don't see in source. The shade plugin filter isn't working because `weld-se-shaded` is an uber jar. The classes inside it are NOT separate artifacts for the shade plugin to filter.\n\nLet me take a different approach: switch from weld-se-shaded to weld-se-core (non-shaded), and also explicitly exclude the old jandex. Additionally, let me check if there might be a hidden compiled class from a previous build:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1087,"cache_read_input_tokens":80947,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1087,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":222},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"e89306d6-b4bf-46f6-8630-3f16a6504b74"}
