{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DA4woBf9ouHxwMbXPGFBFD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Jandex issue is a classic fat-jar problem. The `weld-se-shaded` jar includes the old Jandex classes inside it as part of the uber JAR, and shade plugin filters only work on Maven artifacts, not on classes within an uber JAR.\n\nThe fix is to switch to non-shaded Weld artifacts: `weld-se-core` and `weld-servlet-core`. This will let Maven properly manage the Jandex dependency versions. Also, I notice `EntityManagerFactoryProducer` in the stack trace - this must be a class from a library. Let me switch to non-shaded Weld:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":552,"cache_read_input_tokens":82034,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":552,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":662},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"35e23e5a-f425-40d7-a674-992a1b14cd0e"}
