{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01N4MMFA8Woipu1ypGKJ4i8y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CDI injection in the resource classes is not working. `this.createUser` is null in `UsersResource`. This means the `@Inject` fields are not being injected. The issue is that when RESTEasy creates the resource instances via `getClasses()`, it creates new instances directly rather than having CDI manage them. The Application class is returning classes (not CDI instances) so RESTEasy uses its own instance creation.\n\nI need to investigate - the `RestApplication` class that's being discovered might be registering classes as unmanaged. The issue is that when using `getClasses()` in the JAX-RS Application, RESTEasy creates instances without CDI. I need to either:\n1. Use `getSingletons()` (but that requires CDI-managed instances)\n2. Or make RESTEasy use CDI for creating instances via the CDI injector factory\n\nSince we're using `resteasy-cdi` with `CdiInjectorFactory`, the resources should be CDI-managed. But the `RestApplication` class registered via `getClasses()` may bypass this.\n\nLet me look at the `RealWorldApplication` and the `RestApplication` to understand what's happening. Actually - let me check if there's a `RestApplication.java` I missed:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1382,"cache_read_input_tokens":109835,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1382,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":430},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"252dfa41-a2b7-46e6-ab3a-6957102f88a4"}
