{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NA4QWxzJZv4Xor3JUj55ur","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→import java.util.HashSet;\n     6→import java.util.Set;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.JwtAuthFilter;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.BusinessExceptionMapper;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.ValidationExceptionMapper;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.CorsFilter;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.JacksonConfig;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.SecurityFilter;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TransactionFilter;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationPath(\"/\")\n    17→public class RealWorldApplication extends Application {\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public Set<Class<?>> getClasses() {\n    21→        Set<Class<?>> classes = new HashSet<>();\n    22→        // Resources\n    23→        classes.add(ArticlesResource.class);\n    24→        classes.add(UsersResource.class);\n    25→        classes.add(UserResource.class);\n    26→        classes.add(ProfilesResource.class);\n    27→        classes.add(TagsResource.class);\n    28→        classes.add(HealthResource.class);\n    29→\n    30→        // Providers\n    31→        classes.add(JwtAuthFilter.class);\n    32→        classes.add(SecurityFilter.class);\n    33→        classes.add(BusinessExceptionMapper.class);\n    34→        classes.add(ValidationExceptionMapper.class);\n    35→        classes.add(CorsFilter.class);\n    36→        classes.add(JacksonConfig.class);\n    37→        classes.add(TransactionFilter.class);\n    38→\n    39→        return classes;\n    40→    }\n    41→}\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"ec601f6c-f39b-4bcc-9f94-f0da9371f994"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01AzrdfjL4J78BNLoJXJD8rH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The logs show `RestApplication` is being used, but our class is `RealWorldApplication`. There must be a `RestApplication` in the classpath (possibly from `resteasy-undertow-cdi`). \n\nThe real CDI injection issue: when RESTEasy uses classes from `getClasses()`, it creates the instances itself (NOT via CDI). To get CDI injection working, the resources should NOT be returned via `getClasses()`. Instead, the CdiInjectorFactory should handle creating CDI-managed instances.\n\nLooking at the logs more carefully: `org.example.realworldapi.RestApplication` - this is in our package namespace! There must be a compiled `.class` file for it somewhere that got into the fat JAR. Let me also check if `resteasy-undertow-cdi` provides auto-discovery.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to not use `getClasses()` at all and rely on RESTEasy's scanning + CDI injection. Or use an empty Application class and let RESTEasy discover @Path-annotated classes via CDI. Let me fix the Main.java to not specify an application class, and instead register resources directly on the deployment:\n\nActually, let me take a different approach. The issue is that there's a `RestApplication` class being discovered. This is likely coming from the resteasy-undertow-cdi module. The real problem is that CDI injection doesn't work with `getClasses()` - RESTEasy creates instances without going through CDI.\n\nThe fix is: DON'T override `getClasses()`. Instead, return an empty set and let `resteasy-cdi` discover and inject resources automatically via CDI. With `bean-discovery-mode=\"all\"`, all `@Path` annotated classes will be discovered by CDI and RESTEasy-CDI will pick them up."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":866,"cache_read_input_tokens":112123,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":866,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1089},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"91cee0cb-76d2-4df5-ac8c-2dda3d4ec0e2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01AzrdfjL4J78BNLoJXJD8rH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01RFNT7KMDn3vz8Wqnqiw1S1","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/RealWorldApplication.java","old_string":"package org.example.realworldapi;\n\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\nimport java.util.HashSet;\nimport java.util.Set;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.JwtAuthFilter;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.BusinessExceptionMapper;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.ValidationExceptionMapper;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.CorsFilter;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.JacksonConfig;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.SecurityFilter;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TransactionFilter;\n\n@ApplicationPath(\"/\")\npublic class RealWorldApplication extends Application {\n\n    @Override\n    public Set<Class<?>> getClasses() {\n        Set<Class<?>> classes = new HashSet<>();\n        // Resources\n        classes.add(ArticlesResource.class);\n        classes.add(UsersResource.class);\n        classes.add(UserResource.class);\n        classes.add(ProfilesResource.class);\n        classes.add(TagsResource.class);\n        classes.add(HealthResource.class);\n\n        // Providers\n        classes.add(JwtAuthFilter.class);\n        classes.add(SecurityFilter.class);\n        classes.add(BusinessExceptionMapper.class);\n        classes.add(ValidationExceptionMapper.class);\n        classes.add(CorsFilter.class);\n        classes.add(JacksonConfig.class);\n        classes.add(TransactionFilter.class);\n\n        return classes;\n    }\n}","new_string":"package org.example.realworldapi;\n\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n\n@ApplicationPath(\"/\")\npublic class RealWorldApplication extends Application {\n    // Empty - let RESTEasy-CDI discover @Path resources and @Provider classes automatically\n}"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":866,"cache_read_input_tokens":112123,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":866,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1089},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"3eec8332-f7f2-4d67-a916-a89be47834bd"}
