{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FGGgZSsvRZef2qTxZvY1o1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.se.SeContainer;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.se.SeContainerInitializer;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManagerFactory;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Persistence;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     8→import org.jboss.resteasy.cdi.CdiInjectorFactory;\n     9→import org.jboss.resteasy.plugins.server.undertow.UndertowJaxrsServer;\n    10→import org.jboss.resteasy.core.ResteasyDeploymentImpl;\n    11→import org.jboss.resteasy.spi.ResteasyDeployment;\n    12→import io.undertow.Undertow;\n    13→import io.undertow.servlet.Servlets;\n    14→import io.undertow.servlet.api.DeploymentInfo;\n    15→import org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.Listener;\n    16→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    17→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    18→\n    19→public class Main {\n    20→\n    21→    private static final Logger LOG = LoggerFactory.getLogger(Main.class);\n    22→\n    23→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    24→        LOG.info(\"Starting RealWorld API application...\");\n    25→\n    26→        // Initialize Weld CDI container\n    27→        SeContainerInitializer initializer = SeContainerInitializer.newInstance();\n    28→        SeContainer container = initializer.initialize();\n    29→\n    30→        // Initialize JPA\n    31→        EntityManagerFactory emf = container.select(EntityManagerFactory.class).get();\n    32→        LOG.info(\"EntityManagerFactory initialized: {}\", emf != null);\n    33→\n    34→        // Setup RESTEasy with Undertow\n    35→        UndertowJaxrsServer server = new UndertowJaxrsServer();\n    36→\n    37→        ResteasyDeployment deployment = new ResteasyDeploymentImpl();\n    38→        deployment.setInjectorFactoryClass(CdiInjectorFactory.class.getName());\n    39→        deployment.setApplicationClass(RealWorldApplication.class.getName());\n    40→\n    41→        DeploymentInfo di = server.undertowDeployment(deployment, \"/api\");\n    42→        di.setClassLoader(Main.class.getClassLoader());\n    43→        di.setContextPath(\"/\");\n    44→        di.setDeploymentName(\"RealWorldAPI\");\n    45→        di.addListener(Servlets.listener(Listener.class));\n    46→\n    47→        int port = Integer.parseInt(System.getProperty(\"server.port\", \"8080\"));\n    48→\n    49→        server.deploy(di);\n    50→        server.start(\n    51→            Undertow.builder()\n    52→                .addHttpListener(port, \"0.0.0.0\")\n    53→        );\n    54→\n    55→        LOG.info(\"RealWorld API started on port {}\", port);\n    56→        LOG.info(\"API available at http://0.0.0.0:{}/api\", port);\n    57→\n    58→        // Add shutdown hook\n    59→        Runtime.getRuntime().addShutdownHook(new Thread(() -> {\n    60→            LOG.info(\"Shutting down...\");\n    61→            server.stop();\n    62→            container.close();\n    63→        }));\n    64→    }\n    65→}\n    66→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"9e48094d-a4e2-4a8b-a753-ed0debd67321"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01W4AWaPmsuH9Tzzq31Zuzhv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Main.java looks good - it uses `CdiInjectorFactory` and `RealWorldApplication.class.getName()`. But in the logs we saw `RestApplication` being used instead. There's likely another Application class in the classpath being picked up.\n\nLet me also check what the `RestApplication` class is. It might be auto-generated by `resteasy-undertow-cdi`. Let me also check - perhaps the Weld CDI servlet listener is using servlet discovery which finds a `web.xml` with `RestApplication` somewhere, or it's being handled by Weld.\n\nActually, looking at the full grep output more carefully, my `RealWorldApplication` IS being set in the deployment. But perhaps `resteasy-undertow-cdi` replaces it. The key issue is CDI injection in resources. Let me take a different, simpler approach - use the `deploy(Application)` method of `UndertowJaxrsServer` instead:\n\nActually, the core issue is very clear: **CDI isn't managing the resource instances**. This happens because when RESTEasy processes `getClasses()`, it creates new instances using `new`. The fix with an empty Application and CdiInjectorFactory should work. Let me rebuild and test:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1183,"cache_read_input_tokens":114474,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1183,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":413},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"533c4e4d-87da-41af-949a-9259b01421f3"}
