{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01EVX8i97mZ9xRJcyiQDSq5K","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `NewUserRequest` has `@JsonRootName(\"user\")`. The request body `{\"user\":{...}}` should match. The issue is likely that the custom `ObjectMapper` from `ApplicationConfiguration` (which has `WRAP_ROOT_VALUE` / `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` enabled) is NOT being used by RESTEasy for deserialization. Instead, RESTEasy uses its own default Jackson provider.\n\nMy `JacksonConfig` provider is a `ContextResolver<ObjectMapper>` but the `ApplicationConfiguration` also produces `ObjectMapper` beans. Let me check the `JacksonConfig`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":754,"cache_read_input_tokens":138443,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":754,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":268},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cccbbd3-df4b-4bdc-8bbb-45d794239170","uuid":"41797524-083f-47fb-ad6e-f853ec92c6fa"}
